ca.eandb.jmist.framework.accel

Interface Grid3.Visitor

  • Enclosing class:
    Grid3

    public static interface Grid3.Visitor
    An interface to allow Grid3.intersect(Ray3, Interval, ca.eandb.jmist.framework.accel.Grid3.Visitor) to notify the caller about each cell passed through by the ray.
    See Also:
    Grid3.intersect(Ray3, Interval, ca.eandb.jmist.framework.accel.Grid3.Visitor)

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      boolean visit(Ray3 ray, Interval I, Grid3.Cell cell)
      Notifies the caller to Grid3.intersect that the ray has passed through the specified cell.

    • Method Detail

      • visit

        boolean visit(Ray3 ray,
              Interval I,
              Grid3.Cell cell)
        Notifies the caller to Grid3.intersect that the ray has passed through the specified cell. It is guaranteed that grid.hasCellAt(cell.getX(), cell.getY(), cell.getZ()) will return true.
        Parameters:
        ray - The ray passed to Grid3.intersect(Ray3, Interval, ca.eandb.jmist.framework.accel.Grid3.Visitor)
        I - The interval along the ray that passes through the cell (i.e., cell.getBoundingBox().contains(ray.pointAt(t)) if and only if I.contains(t)).
        cell - The cell being traversed.
        Returns:
        A value indicating whether Grid3.intersect(Ray3, Interval, ca.eandb.jmist.framework.accel.Grid3.Visitor) should continue its traversal.
        See Also:
        Grid3.intersect(Ray3, Interval, ca.eandb.jmist.framework.accel.Grid3.Visitor), Grid3.Cell.getBoundingBox(), Box3.contains(Point3), Ray3.pointAt(double), Interval.contains(double), Grid3.hasCellAt(int, int, int)
